696	/// otherwise the flag's documented default string (recorded when the bare
697	/// flag is given).  A `flagOpt` flag NEVER consumes a separate following
698	/// token — that token stays positional.  This mirrors
699	/// `System.Console.CmdArgs.Explicit.flagOpt`, used by HS for `--bound`,
700	/// `--output`, `--with-maude`, etc.  Verified against the installed HS
701	/// binary: `tamarin-prover --bound 5 t.spthy` treats `5` as a positional
